Nushell, or Nu for short, is a new shell that takes a modern, structured approach to your commandline. It works seamlessly with the data from your filesystem, operating system, and a growing number of file formats to make it easy to build powerful commandline pipelines.
Today, we're releasing 0.16 of Nu
íźźŕpTitle: title: Nushell 0.16.0
Path: Nushell 0.16.0
Content:




Nushell, or Nu for short, is a new shell that takes a modern, structured approach to your commandline. It works seamlessly with the data from your filesystem, operating system, and a growing number of file formats to make it easy to build powerful commandline pipelines.
Today, we're releasing 0.16 of Nu
óŔXarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2020-06-30-nushell_0_16_0.mdŔ@d79e53a26cdebb8d29df7c42fdfcbf4f86448463bad257c3feedc3572a12aed1Ķtitle: Nushell 0.16.0ĎĮWhere to get itŕŖNu 0.16.0 is available as 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/releases/tag/0.16.0] pre-built binaries
 or from 
[link: https://crates.io/crates/nu] crates.io
. If you have Rust installed you can install it using 
``cargo install nu``
.
If you want more goodies, you can install 
``cargo install nu --features=stable``
.
As part of this release, we also publish a set of plugins you can install and use with Nu. To install, use 
``cargo install nu_plugin_<plugin name>``
.
íźźŕTitle: title: Nushell 0.16.0
Path: Where to get it
Content:
Nu 0.16.0 is available as 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/releases/tag/0.16.0] pre-built binaries
 or from 
[link: https://crates.io/crates/nu] crates.io
. If you have Rust installed you can install it using 
``cargo install nu``
.
If you want more goodies, you can install 
``cargo install nu --features=stable``
.
As part of this release, we also publish a set of plugins you can install and use with Nu. To install, use 
``cargo install nu_plugin_<plugin name>``
.
óŔXarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2020-06-30-nushell_0_16_0.mdŔ@48597b7d0a789a28a8b45e66b913594d4aca64b49b0a6afb6aae8b7aa40c236eĶtitle: Nushell 0.16.0ĎŔANew automated release binaries (charlespierce, fdncred, sophiajt)ŕDUp to this point, we've hand-rolled all the binary releases. The process has been time-consuming and error-prone. Starting with 0.16.0, we'll be releasing using the GitHub release automation. The first benefits you'll see is that we've also added a wix-based installer for Windows users. The second, perhaps harder to see, benefit is a more relaxed release process that's easier on the project maintainers :)
Please note: as part of this, we took the opportunity to also align the directory structure across platforms. Apologies in advance for any inconvenience this might cause.
íźźŕ≤Title: title: Nushell 0.16.0
Path: New automated release binaries (charlespierce, fdncred, sophiajt)
Content:
Up to this point, we've hand-rolled all the binary releases. The process has been time-consuming and error-prone. Starting with 0.16.0, we'll be releasing using the GitHub release automation. The first benefits you'll see is that we've also added a wix-based installer for Windows users. The second, perhaps harder to see, benefit is a more relaxed release process that's easier on the project maintainers :)
Please note: as part of this, we took the opportunity to also align the directory structure across platforms. Apologies in advance for any inconvenience this might cause.
óŔXarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2020-06-30-nushell_0_16_0.mdŔ@51abbdec0c1c221a7c3cd84cf516d71e93b60042473cd85939f5238dad9ea9f9Ķtitle: Nushell 0.16.0Ď∂New textview (fdncred)ŕ5We've had a few requests for an improved text viewing experience, so with 0.16.0 we're trying out a new viewer based on the 
[link: https://crates.io/crates/bat] bat
 crate. We also support quite a lot of 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2010] configuration settings
 for this new text viewer.
íźźŕxTitle: title: Nushell 0.16.0
Path: New textview (fdncred)
Content:
We've had a few requests for an improved text viewing experience, so with 0.16.0 we're trying out a new viewer based on the 
[link: https://crates.io/crates/bat] bat
 crate. We also support quite a lot of 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2010] configuration settings
 for this new text viewer.
óŔXarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2020-06-30-nushell_0_16_0.mdŔ@ef514fea1621b1a3e4fa8fe2dd0ad5f5f462983e94aaef1bfbbd56e5d94286c0Ķtitle: Nushell 0.16.0ĎĮ (JosephTLyons)ŕ4``random``
We have a new top-level command: 
``random``
. To start, there are three sub-commands:
``random uuid``
 - generate random UUIDs
``random bool``
 - a random "coin flip" with optional bias
``random dice``
 - roll a single or a set of dice, optionally setting the number of sides and number of dices
íźźŕpTitle: title: Nushell 0.16.0
Path:  (JosephTLyons)
Content:
``random``
We have a new top-level command: 
``random``
. To start, there are three sub-commands:
``random uuid``
 - generate random UUIDs
``random bool``
 - a random "coin flip" with optional bias
``random dice``
 - roll a single or a set of dice, optionally setting the number of sides and number of dices
óŔXarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2020-06-30-nushell_0_16_0.mdŔ@267e8421316e0653ebe2d98211e0f20280687a91067309392a5efd06d05578bdĶtitle: Nushell 0.16.0ĎŔ- (JosephTLyons, arashout, andrasio, amousa11)ŕ£``math``
We've consolidated and added to our math operations. Now available as part of the 0.16.0 release:
``math avg``
 - averages a list of numbers
``math sum``
 - totals a list of numbers
``math mode``
 - gets the mode of a list of numbers
``math median``
 - gets the median of a list of numbers
``math min``
 - gets the minimum value of a list of numbers
``math max``
 - gets the maximum value of a list of numbers
íźźŕżTitle: title: Nushell 0.16.0
Path:  (JosephTLyons, arashout, andrasio, amousa11)
Content:
``math``
We've consolidated and added to our math operations. Now available as part of the 0.16.0 release:
``math avg``
 - averages a list of numbers
``math sum``
 - totals a list of numbers
``math mode``
 - gets the mode of a list of numbers
``math median``
 - gets the median of a list of numbers
``math min``
 - gets the minimum value of a list of numbers
``math max``
 - gets the maximum value of a list of numbers
óŔXarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2020-06-30-nushell_0_16_0.mdŔ@8e021a38ddbba0ea728074c23eb8ebfdfac2014502eabe3096d98d9789554f6fĶtitle: Nushell 0.16.0ĎģOther commandsŕO[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1992] ``every``
 - lets you skip every n-rows (kubouch)
``ansi``
 - lets you output ANSI color codes to color your strings (sophiajt, fdncred)
``char``
 - makes it possible to output newlines and tabs (sophiajt)
``do``
 - runs a block to completion, optionally ignoring errors (sophiajt)
