Path: RFC process (jzaefferer)
Content:
We now have an 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/rfcs] RFC process
 if you want to propose new features and breaking changes to Nu. Come let us know what you think and share your vision with us.
óŔXarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2020-06-30-nushell_0_16_0.mdŔ@ab2525bc996cbe1d6732a4995c20e5766c5a623780361634f3da03d5e6672d8bĶtitle: Nushell 0.16.0ĎŔ#Starship becomes optional (fdncred)ŕ≤We've made enabling starship a configuration option, rather than always being on. This allows you to opt-in, if you'd like the starship experience, but removes the requirement that you have to know to build without starship if you'd rather not have it (which may not be possible if you're using binary releases).
To enable starship, set the 
``use_starship``
 setting:
```Fenced(Borrowed(""))
> config --set [use_starship $true]

```
íźźŕTitle: title: Nushell 0.16.0
Path: Starship becomes optional (fdncred)
Content:
We've made enabling starship a configuration option, rather than always being on. This allows you to opt-in, if you'd like the starship experience, but removes the requirement that you have to know to build without starship if you'd rather not have it (which may not be possible if you're using binary releases).
To enable starship, set the 
``use_starship``
 setting:
```Fenced(Borrowed(""))
> config --set [use_starship $true]

```
